    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-11-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-11-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="615"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d615">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Pera</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-11-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 7, 1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Rifaat Pasha appointed Grand Vizier; Tewfik Pasha, minister for foreign affairs.
                    Vali of Aleppo replaced by Kiamil Pasha.</p>
                <p>Five thousand men reported killed at Diarbekir, of whom 2,300 Mussulmans. Porte
                    says this is exaggerated. It is generally believed that in various places 10,000
                    have been killed in a month. No killing of women or children reported.</p>
                <pb facs="0602" n="1336" xml:id="pg_1336"/>
                <p>If central government lose control, through its rapid changes, I fear for
                    missionaries. None yet killed. We should have stronger naval forces in eastern
                    Mediterranean.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Terrell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
